                                        <u>
                                            <b>Article (1):</b>
                                        </u>
                                        <br/>
                                        The Preamble shall be considered as an integral part of the agreement.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <u>
                                            <b>Article (2): Obligations:</b>
                                        </u>
                                        <br/>
                                        <u>Obligations of the “First Party”:</u>
                                    </p>
                                    <ol style="margin-left:15px;">
                                        <li>The “First Party” agrees to provide services herein after referred to in the
                                            schedule (1) according to the terms and provisions contained in this
                                            agreement and in conformity with the laws applicable in the United Arab
                                            Emirates.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            The “First Party” undertakes to provide the “Second Party” with the
                                            professional services requested according to the terms and conditions and in
                                            conformity with the articles and annexes contained in this agreement.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            The “First Party” shall not disclose to a “Third Party” any confidential
                                            information or documents related to the Second Party. The “First Party”
                                            undertakes to use such information for the purpose of executing the services
                                            requested in the contract which maintain the “Second Party” rights. The
                                            “First Party” shall not disclose or share such information to any competitor
                                            to the “Second Party”, however the “First Party” has the right to use such
                                            information and documents before the concerned governmental institutions and
                                            to submit them whenever necessary and in accordance with the duties of the
                                            “First Party”.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            The “First Party” may not assume his duties and commitments due to force
                                            majeure which prevented him from implementing such commitments.
                                        </li>
                                    </ol>

                                    <p>
                                        <u>Obligations of the “Second Party”</u>
                                    </p>
                                    <ol style="margin-left:15px;">
                                        <li>The “Second Party” undertakes to provide the “First Party” with all the
                                            information requested to execute the services he is entitled to provide.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>The “Second Party” undertakes to provide the “First Party” with opening
                                            balances for all ledgers.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>The “Second Party” herein declares that all the information submitted to the
                                            “First party is true and accurate. In case of giving any false information,
                                            the “Second Party” shall bear –solely- the legal consequences that may
                                            arise.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>In case the “Second Party” desires to terminate this contract, the “Second
                                            Party” shall give the 3 months written notice to the “First Party”, failure
                                            of this, the “First Party” is entitled to claim the total contract fees as
                                            agreed and the “Second Party” shall do the payment in full.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>In case the payment is delayed by the “Second Party” according to the
                                            payments scheduled dates contained in “Schedule 1” and for the maximum
                                            period of 5 working days from the due date, the “First party” is entitled to
                                            suspend the work and the “Second Party” shall bear all the legal
                                            consequences that may arise and shall pay all the amounts due.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>Payments shall be done in advance by cheques according to its due dates
                                            herein contained in “Schedule 1”.
                                        </li>
                                    </ol>
                                    <p>
                                        <b>Article (3) Term of the Contract</b>
                                        <br/>
                                        This contract shall be valid from
                                        <b t-field="o.date_start"/>
                                        and shall be renewable for similar periods
