                                            <b>Article (5) General Provisions:</b>
                                        </u>
                                    </p>
                                    <ol style="margin-left:15px;">
                                        <li>The First Party has the right to enter into subcontracting with a third
                                            party to fulfil its commitments contained in this contract. The First Party
                                            is obliged to pay the financial dues against the works done by the third
                                            party. The Second party has no liability towards any subcontracting executed
                                            by the First Party and the First Party is obliged to submit the services as
                                            per the provisions contained in this contract.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>The Second Party shall have no right to recruit any of the First Party’s
                                            employees for work for two years from contract’s expiry date and the First
                                            Party has the right to claim re-compensation from the Second Party in case
                                            this item is violated by the Second Party.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>As per the terms and provisions contained in this contract, the First Party
                                            has the right to provide new clients the same services previously offered
                                            for other clients.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>The “Second Party” shall authorize the “First Party” to act on his behalf in
                                            front of the Federal Tax Authority with regards to registration, tax filing,
                                            budgets, balance sheets as well as all other transactions.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>Any change or amendments which might occur to this contract shall be
                                            approved in written and signed by both parties.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>The “Second Party” shall have no right to transfer any part or item
                                            contained in this contract to any other party.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>The “First Party” shall have no liability in case the “Second Party” used
                                            –by any means- the data/information resulted from the services provided by
